The Chinese government uses a variety of encryption algorithms and decryption methods to protect its classified communication. Some of these include AES (Advanced Encryption Standard), Blowfish, CAST128, DES (Data Encryption Standard), IDEA (International Data Encryption Algorithm), RC4, Serpent, and TripleDES. These algorithms use different key lengths ranging from 64-bit to 512-bit keys depending on the sensitivity of the data being transmitted. Additionally, the Chinese government may also employ steganography techniques to hide messages within images or other media files.
